  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a pan over medium heat. Add cumin seeds and mustard seeds and let sizzle. Add chopped onion and saut\u00105 until softened. Add grated ginger and minced garlic and cook for 1 minute. Add sliced eggplant and cook until tender. Add nuka-pickle and stir well. Add coconut milk, turmeric, salt, sugar and cardamom powder. Stir well and let simmer for 10 minutes. Taste and adjust seasoning.",
    "Serve warm or chilled, garnished with fresh cilantro if desired."
